{"id":33235,"date":"2025-06-10T19:13:19","date_gmt":"2025-06-10T13:43:19","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.verdantis.com\/?p=33235"},"modified":"2025-07-04T14:19:15","modified_gmt":"2025-07-04T08:49:15","slug":"bom-inventory-management-software","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.verdantis.com\/bom-inventory-management-software\/","title":{"rendered":"Inventory &#038; Bill of Materials Management Software"},"content":{"rendered":"\t\t<div data-elementor-type=\"wp-post\" data-elementor-id=\"33235\" class=\"elementor elementor-33235\" data-elementor-post-type=\"post\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-81128e9 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"81128e9\" data-element_type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-9dac256 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"9dac256\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>A bill of materials (BOM) is nothing but a detailed list of input materials, parts, components and even consumables that make up a final finished product.<\/p><p>The product development, design or engineering team at any given company is generally tasked with the job of maintaining an accurate Bill of Materials throughout a products&#8217; lifecycle.<\/p><p>As an example; here are a few line items that are part of a standard Bill of Materials document;<\/p><ul><li><strong>Input Materials<\/strong>: In case of an Automotive component manufacturer, this can be steel. In case of a confectionary manufacturer, this can be flour, cocoa etc<\/li><li><strong>Spare Parts<\/strong>: In case of an smartphone manufacturer, this can be the buttons or keypads used.<\/li><li><strong>Consumables<\/strong>: Usage of consumables like Grease, Oil, Glue, Wire etc\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0<\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d366eed elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"d366eed\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Types of BOM Inventory Management Software<\/h2>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-92162ad elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"92162ad\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p class=\"\" data-start=\"228\" data-end=\"688\">When one talks about management of a Bills of Materials with the Inventory Management System; it can typically mean 2 things, depending on whether you&#8217;re the manufacturer or the consumer.\u00a0<\/p><p class=\"\" data-start=\"228\" data-end=\"688\">1. <b>As the Consumer<\/b> &#8211; In this particular instance, you are the consumer of the product for which the BOM is issued. Companies with massive production operations across several countries use several fixed assets and movable assets, each with their own BOMs and maintenance schedules.\u00a0<\/p><p class=\"\" data-start=\"228\" data-end=\"688\">A BOM management software in this case synchronizes the BOM with the inventory management system and supports an <a href=\"https:\/\/www.verdantis.com\/mro-inventory-management\/\">overarching MRO inventory management<\/a> strategy.<\/p><p class=\"\" data-start=\"228\" data-end=\"688\">2. <b>As the Manufacturer &#8211; <\/b>In this instance, you are manufacturing the same product for which the BOM is issued and you need to update the required inventory levels of raw materials, consumables, spare parts etc required for manufacturing the given product.\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-819e702 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"819e702\" data-element_type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a19a98b elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"a19a98b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Equipment [Asset] BOMs &amp; Inventory Management<\/h2>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c6e7092 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"c6e7092\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>As in case 1 above, analyzing BOMs, extracting key data and mapping the same across source systems is of key importance for Asset Management &amp; MRO teams.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-bf213a3 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"bf213a3\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>The information captured via the BOM, specifically the equipment and spare part data is then fed into an ERP system into any of the following modules.\u00a0 \u00a0<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-89cd2eb elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"89cd2eb\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<ul data-start=\"2360\" data-end=\"2720\"><li class=\"\" data-start=\"2360\" data-end=\"2458\"><p class=\"\" data-start=\"2362\" data-end=\"2458\"><b>An MRO Spare Parts Master<\/b>\u00a0\u2013 Typically resides in the ERP, a database of all spare parts, across different facilities\u00a0\u00a0<\/p><\/li><li class=\"\" data-start=\"2459\" data-end=\"2546\"><p class=\"\" data-start=\"2461\" data-end=\"2546\"><strong data-start=\"2461\" data-end=\"2501\">An Asset Master<\/strong>\u00a0\u2013 Also resides in the ERP, this is a database of all fixed assets across different facilities.\u00a0<\/p><\/li><li class=\"\" data-start=\"2547\" data-end=\"2623\"><p class=\"\" data-start=\"2549\" data-end=\"2623\"><strong data-start=\"2549\" data-end=\"2565\">A Digital Record of Equipment BOM<\/strong> \u2013 Maintenance &amp; asset management teams maintain a digital record of asset BOMs in the ERP<\/p><\/li><li class=\"\" data-start=\"2624\" data-end=\"2720\"><p class=\"\" data-start=\"2626\" data-end=\"2720\"><b>A Digital Record of Work Orders<\/b>\u00a0\u2013 Similarly, MRO teams also maintain an up to date record of all digital work orders for every piece of equipment to understand the historical context behind the maintenance schedules\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0\u00a0<\/p><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-51265ee elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"51265ee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>For companies in asset-intensive business with heavy production or manufacturing operations, ensuring seamless maintenance operations is the cornerstone for building operational efficiency.<\/p><p>To enable this; management of spare parts data, it&#8217;s inventory levels and its dependency across the fixed assets in the organization needs to be mapped in real-time.\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-dd06704 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"dd06704\" data-element_type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-1cb43c4 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"1cb43c4\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Extracting Data from Equipment BOM<\/h2>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c9fc198 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"c9fc198\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>One of the key capabilities A BOM and inventory management software, in this context, is one that can extract data from a Bill of Materials document, including;<\/p>\n<p>1. Spare Parts required for the upkeep or maintenance of any given piece of product, along with relevant spare part details like Manufacturer Name or Manufacturer Part Number<\/p>\n<p>2. Details of the equipment\/fixed asset, including Equipment Category, equipment number etc&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>3. Consumables required for equipment upkeep<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2066677 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"2066677\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Thanks to advanced AI technologies and agentic frameworks, it is now possible to extract data from unstructured documents.\u00a0<\/p><p>This enables organizations to identify spare parts for MRO required throughout the course of the lifecycle of\u00a0 an equipment<\/p><p>The video below showcases how this structured data can be extracted from a Bill of Materials document, or in fact, any technical document.\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-f196cf3 elementor-widget elementor-widget-video\" data-id=\"f196cf3\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;youtube_url&quot;:&quot;https:\\\/\\\/www.youtube.com\\\/watch?v=XHOmBV4js_E&quot;,&quot;video_type&quot;:&quot;youtube&quot;,&quot;controls&quot;:&quot;yes&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"video.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-wrapper elementor-open-inline\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-video\"><\/div>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-14984b0 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"14984b0\" data-element_type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7413faa elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"7413faa\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Updating the Data to Master Data Systems<\/h2>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-509edff elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"509edff\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>The second step is to create these SKUs in the MRO master.\u00a0<\/p><p>An MRO master is simply a dataset that maintains a dump of all the spare parts that are required for equipment upkeep.<\/p><p>After extracting the sparts information of every piece of equipment, there are 2 possible scenarios.<\/p><p>1. <b>Spare Part Exists in the MRO Master<\/b> &#8211; In this case, the inventory management system will detect that the same spare part already exists in the MRO master. Here, the part record and the asset record will be updated in the MRO master and the equipment master respectively to map dependency between the 2.<\/p><p>2. <b>Spare Part doesn&#8217;t Exist in the MRO Master<\/b> &#8211; In this case, a new MRO data record will be created and pushed for approval. During creation itself, the dependent equipment will be mapped against the spare part.\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0\u00a0<\/p><p>This information is maintained in the MRO master <a href=\"https:\/\/www.verdantis.com\/asset-master-data-management\/\">or asset master<\/a>, which acts like a bridge between the inventory management system and the bill of materials data.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-09b5f10 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"09b5f10\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>The MRO master can then be looked up against the inventory management system in any of the ERPs for an accurate view into the number of spare parts available against any given piece of equipment\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0\u00a0<\/p><p>Just a few years ago, this data management across BOMs and Inventory Management Systems was simply not possible since BOM documents shared by several suppliers can be unstructured and all over the place.<\/p><p>But with the advent of AI-based technologies, software systems are now &#8220;context-aware&#8221; and they can fetch structured information from unstructured sources and process them with other disparate systems.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a41265b e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"a41265b\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8c8e99c elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8c8e99c\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Conclusion<\/h2>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-5f4b5ee elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"5f4b5ee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Managing BOM information and spare parts Inventory is a an ideal process for enterprise asset management.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p><p>With the introduction of novel agentic systems, this information can be &#8220;understood&#8221; and synchronized across systems\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>A bill of materials (BOM) is nothing but a detailed list of input materials, parts, components and even consumables that make up a final finished product. The product development, design or engineering team at any given company is generally tasked with the job of maintaining an accurate Bill of Materials throughout a products&#8217; lifecycle. As [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":5,"featured_media":29947,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"inline_featured_image":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[64],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-33235","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-blog"],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.verdantis.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/33235","targetHints":{"a